<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99790590758600></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99790590758600><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=99790590758600>RE: Help me out plz...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=99790590758600#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 15th 4:05 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Personally, I would rather play as a Gnome due to the ease of acquiring items, the newbie areas of BB, Gfay, AND SF, you start wit Infravision (Although that's not a big deal... just get a harvester if you're an Erudite), the INT is decent, and you're not KOS to all the lighties (Never taken my Necro over to a darky camp or anything, dunno if you're KOS to those...).&nbsp;&nbsp;Although, you do have to be careful at lower levels in Kelethin -- you WILL be KOS to the Ashwoods, right above the bank... and if you keel one elf (Duel or if you're on a PvP server), you'll be KOS to all of Kelethin =(<br><br>Oh, and the reasons I'd start an Erudite are that, in most cases, you will not be doing ANY melee, therefore you can sacrifice the str/sta/agi/dex that the other classes have over you for a great starting INT.<br><br>The stats for a Necro are:<br><br>INT -- As much as possible!  INT gear is not cheap, and a high INT at lower levels is extremely useful as it effects your max mana.<br><br>STR -- This is useless -- STR gear is cheap, and you won't need it unless you find something that weighs 100 lb... your gear (armor/weapons) is light.<br><br>AGI -- This can be fairly usefull -- especially if you screw up while kiting.  If you're attacked, AGI effects the chances of them hitting you and the damage done.<br><br>DEX -- Useless, that is all =P<br><br>WIS -- Useless, that is all =P<br><br>CHA -- Do NOT, I mean, do NOT buff this up -- even WITH items.  As a Necromancer, your CHA is supposed to be as low as possible -- Fear, a few DoTs, and some other spells use CHA as a part of determining if the spell will stick or not -- yet Necromancers, need LESS CHA, as opposed to Bards and Enchanters.<br><br>STA -- This can be useful as it will give you a bit more HP, but usually isn't useful until the higher levels (Much higher...).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
